OL,3,CRetailers caught selling e-scooters
OL,4,Cfor 'commuting' despite road ban
OL,6,FMajor British retailers have been
OL,7,Fselling e-scooters for "commuting"
OL,8,Fdespite warnings from police and
OL,9,Fcoroners that it is illegal and puts
OL,10,Friders at risk of serious injury or
OL,11,Fdeath.
OL,13,FBrands such as Currys, Argos and
OL,14,FHalfords, as well as online giant
OL,15,FAmazon, used marketing pitches about
OL,16,F"urban riding", getting to work on
OL,17,Ftime, and "long distanced commutes" to
OL,18,Fsell the electric vehicles.
OL,26,@oD@XOUoD@bO]xD@AOUxD@NO]yD@KOUyD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/18
