OL,3,CRetailers caught selling e-scooters
OL,4,Cfor 'commuting' despite road ban
OL,6,FAdverts for e-scooters on the Halfords
OL,7,Fwebsites come with a "legal warning",
OL,8,Fsetting out: "It is illegal to use an
OL,9,Fe-scooter on a public road, pavement,
OL,10,Fcycle lane or bridleway."
OL,12,FBut in the sales pitch for a #499 Pure
OL,13,FEscape e-scooter, the retailer told
OL,14,Fcustomers it has cruise control "for
OL,15,Fadded relaxation across long distanced
OL,16,Fcommutes", while Halfords is also
OL,17,Fselling an #899 McLaren e-scooter for
OL,18,F"urban riding".
OL,26,@oD@VOUoD@dO]pD@NOUrD@YO]vD@aOUxD@IO]zD@
OL,26,AAOUzD@NO]
