OL,3,CRetailers caught selling e-scooters
OL,4,Cfor 'commuting' despite road ban
OL,6,FUnder UK law, rented e-scooters can be
OL,7,Flegally used on the roads by holders
OL,8,Fof a driving licence, but police have
OL,9,Fthe power to stop private e-scooters,
OL,10,Fseize vehicles, and land the user with
OL,11,Fa fine or criminal prosecution for
OL,12,Fdriving without insurance.
OL,14,FResponding to the findings of the
OL,15,Finvestigation, a Department for
OL,16,FTransport spokesperson said: "Despite
OL,17,Fthe laws around the sale and use of e-
OL,18,Fscooters being crystal clear, it is
OL,19,Fextremely disappointing to see major
OL,20,Fretailers continuing to sell e-
OL,21,Fscooters under false pretences.
OL,26,@xD@^OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,305,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30412
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F304A1782893891
OL,3,CRetailers caught selling e-scooters
OL,4,Cfor 'commuting' despite road ban
OL,6,F"We are aware of the safety concerns
OL,7,Fsurrounding e-scooters which is why we
OL,8,Fare looking at how they operate in
OL,9,Ftrial areas across the country so
OL,10,Ffuture legislation keeps both riders
OL,11,Fand pedestrians safe".
OL,13,FAfter the 2022 inquest into the death
OL,14,Fof 14-year-old Fatima Abukar, east
OL,15,FLondon coroner Graeme Irvine issued a
OL,16,F"prevention of future deaths" report
OL,17,Fto police, the government, and e-
OL,18,Fscooter retailers.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@UO]xD@AOUxD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/18
